16:40.215 --> 16:42.882
If you don't fit the mold,
they destroy you.

16:43.802 --> 16:45.184
They destroy you?

16:45.186 --> 16:47.387
You sound like a teenage girl. Grow up.

16:47.389 --> 16:49.255
You grow up. Money isn't magic.

16:49.257 --> 16:51.023
Magical power to pay your rent on time,

16:51.025 --> 16:53.092
- fix your car when it breaks.
- I'm not talking about

16:53.094 --> 16:55.795
money for living, okay?

16:55.797 --> 16:58.431
I'm talking about wealth.

16:58.433 --> 17:00.600
Coaster?

17:00.602 --> 17:01.567
Thank you.

17:01.569 --> 17:03.536
You call it wealth.

17:03.538 --> 17:05.637
I call it the shortcuts
that you got that I didn't.

17:05.640 --> 17:08.273
- I am not some...
- Hey, when I started working

17:08.276 --> 17:11.109
at the car dealership,
you know what the first thing

17:11.112 --> 17:12.878
- I bought was?
- Some gruel to quiet

17:12.881 --> 17:14.547
- your rumbling tummy?
- A Rolex.

17:14.549 --> 17:16.549
Used... "vintage," they called it.

17:16.550 --> 17:18.317
Thing was busted and the
hands didn't even move

17:18.319 --> 17:19.618
and I couldn't afford to fix it.

17:19.621 --> 17:21.454
But when I wore that thing,

17:21.455 --> 17:23.489
people looked at me differently.

17:23.491 --> 17:24.957
Okay? I sold more cars in that first...

17:24.959 --> 17:26.559
Okay, see? You're making my point.

17:26.560 --> 17:31.597
It's stupid to let other people decide
what is okay and what's not.

17:31.599 --> 17:33.399
- That's easy for you to say.
- Okay, um,

17:33.401 --> 17:34.901
I'm gonna find us a
lawyer and you get us

17:34.903 --> 17:37.603
- something real to drink.
- Will do, m'lady.

17:44.078 --> 17:45.411
Afternoon, sir.

17:45.413 --> 17:46.746
Afternoon.

17:46.748 --> 17:48.414
What are you in the mood for?

17:49.198 --> 17:50.683
You have anything with gin?

17:50.685 --> 17:52.852
Might I recommend
the Constable's Lament?

17:52.854 --> 17:56.656
Gin, shaved ginger, cumin.

17:56.658 --> 17:58.424
How about just a gin and tonic?

17:58.426 --> 18:00.793
Yes, sir.

18:04.999 --> 18:06.532
It's ridiculous, right?

18:06.534 --> 18:07.800
I mean, how complicated
does it have to be

18:07.802 --> 18:11.137
- to do some day drinking?
- Yeah, man.

18:11.139 --> 18:13.306
- Yeah, just a G-and-T for me.
- Exactly.

18:13.308 --> 18:15.274
- Yeah.
- I'm Kurt Radcliffe.

18:15.276 --> 18:18.778
- Richard... James.
- Is Anne James your sister?

18:18.780 --> 18:21.347
Afraid not.
No, I'm visiting from back east.

18:21.349 --> 18:23.282
- You a member here?
- Yeah.

18:23.284 --> 18:25.818
I had my first drink right
here at this very bar.

18:25.820 --> 18:28.321
- Wow.
- Yeah. My grampy slipped me

18:28.323 --> 18:30.623
- the last of his Scotch.
- That's awesome.

18:30.625 --> 18:32.959
Well, I was six. He was an asshole.

18:33.280 --> 18:34.280
I'm kidding.

18:34.996 --> 18:36.362
- Actually, I'm not kidding.
- Sure.

18:36.364 --> 18:38.898
He was an asshole, but whatever.

18:38.900 --> 18:40.190
Family is family.

18:40.702 --> 18:42.468
So what do you do?

18:42.470 --> 18:45.371
And I thought, there's no way
this jury's gonna see it our way.

18:45.373 --> 18:46.973
Then all of a sudden, this guy comes in.

18:47.519 --> 18:49.408
I had them eating out of my hand.

18:49.410 --> 18:52.879
- You looking for someone?
- Yeah, a lawyer.

18:53.584 --> 18:55.047
Well...

18:55.049 --> 18:57.416
you've certainly come
to the right place.

18:57.418 --> 18:59.385
- Just look for somebody...
- Who thinks

18:59.387 --> 19:01.754
their opinion is worth $700 an hour.

19:01.756 --> 19:04.023
Well, you clearly know
what you're doing.

19:04.025 --> 19:05.658
You mind if I smoke?

19:05.660 --> 19:07.460
Only if you don't share.

19:12.667 --> 19:14.667
Can we smoke in here?

19:14.669 --> 19:18.070
No. But it really pisses them off.

19:22.010 --> 19:24.377
So you're getting a divorce.

19:24.379 --> 19:26.245
Young woman looking for a lawyer.

19:26.247 --> 19:28.915
No, my marriage split up
a couple years ago.

19:28.917 --> 19:32.018
Yeah, I did that dance twice myself.

19:32.020 --> 19:33.753
Two exes.

19:33.755 --> 19:35.788
One that I like
but never get to talk to.

19:35.790 --> 19:38.190
The other one I can't stand.
Have lunch with him every week.

19:38.192 --> 19:39.625
Do you still see him?

19:39.627 --> 19:42.862
Actually, she wasn't
who I thought she was.

19:42.864 --> 19:46.365
She?

19:46.367 --> 19:48.734
That's one I never tried.

19:50.138 --> 19:52.572
Call the lady!

19:52.574 --> 19:54.307
Nailed it.

19:54.309 --> 19:55.942
It was really something,
you should have...

19:55.944 --> 19:58.377
That one.

19:58.379 --> 20:00.646
Hollis McCallister.

20:00.648 --> 20:02.582
Yeah, he's one of the best
lawyers in Seattle.

20:02.584 --> 20:04.784
- You know him?
- He's good.

20:04.786 --> 20:06.285
But I'm better.

20:08.990 --> 20:11.290
Come on. I had to make sure
that I liked you first.

20:14.395 --> 20:16.128
What do you need?

20:28.682 --> 20:29.723
Ezra?

20:30.279 --> 20:31.243
Ezra?

20:31.245 --> 20:34.347
Hey, I know you.

20:34.349 --> 20:36.282
Ezra, stop. Ezra!

20:38.753 --> 20:41.153
Excuse me?

20:41.155 --> 20:43.956
That was for the dog, not you.

20:43.958 --> 20:45.925
Well, when you disappeared,
he needed a home.

20:45.927 --> 20:50.029
So I bought him and I named him Ezra.

20:51.254 --> 20:53.499
Ezra, come here.

20:53.501 --> 20:55.201
Come on.

20:55.203 --> 20:57.203
Ezra, roll over.

20:57.205 --> 20:59.438
Roll over.

20:59.440 --> 21:01.073
Another Ezra that doesn't listen to me.

21:01.075 --> 21:02.195
That's the story of my life.

21:02.608 --> 21:03.843
Okay.

21:03.845 --> 21:06.946
- What are you doing here?
- Your father invited me.

21:06.948 --> 21:08.981
Said he had some sort of
big announcement to make.

21:08.983 --> 21:11.217
- Yes, so I've heard.
- Yeah, and I'm doing your job

21:11.219 --> 21:13.152
- at the company now, so...
- Really?

21:13.154 --> 21:14.787
No one... no one told me that.

21:14.789 --> 21:18.457
Well, you never call to check in, so...

21:18.459 --> 21:22.194
Right, um, well, I have to say,
I'm glad you went back.

21:22.196 --> 21:24.997
Yeah, me too. I just had to,
like, do my thing, you know?

21:24.999 --> 21:27.566
I learned to tap dance,
I learned photography.

21:27.568 --> 21:29.568
- You made cheese.
- I made cheese.

21:29.570 --> 21:31.337
Yes, I did. I made cheese.

21:31.683 --> 21:36.142
But then I woke up one morning
and I was just like, I'm good.

21:36.144 --> 21:37.710
- Wow.
- Yeah.

21:37.712 --> 21:39.245
And then I called your parents
and your job was open

21:39.247 --> 21:41.080
and that was a big promotion for me.

21:41.082 --> 21:44.717
And I somehow convinced
them to let me try it.

21:44.719 --> 21:48.020
I bet you're doing really great.

21:48.022 --> 21:51.691
Yeah, I am. Thank you.

21:52.700 --> 21:53.700
Ezra, come!

21:54.796 --> 21:57.352
- Don't even say it.
- I was not going to.

21:57.865 --> 21:59.298
Ezra!

22:08.676 --> 22:11.844
Somebody get me Agent
Simons on the phone!

22:11.846 --> 22:13.079
Right now!

22:19.187 --> 22:22.121
Hey. Do you know what doesn't
go with romantic getaways?

22:22.123 --> 22:24.090
<i>- Calls from your coworkers.
- First off,</i>

22:24.092 --> 22:25.891
do not ignore my phone calls.

22:25.893 --> 22:27.893
It's rude. And second, how close are we?

22:27.895 --> 22:29.862
<i>- I'm getting a lot of pressure.
- You're under pressure?</i>

22:29.864 --> 22:31.597
No disrespect,
but I'm the one who's out here

22:31.599 --> 22:32.965
with his ass on the line.

22:32.967 --> 22:34.266
<i>Now listen to me, Agent Simons...</i>

22:34.268 --> 22:36.035
Look, Agent Cook, I made a choice.

22:36.037 --> 22:37.436
<i>- Ha!
- One that I'm confident</i>

22:37.438 --> 22:39.071
will yield results very soon.

22:39.073 --> 22:40.272
<i>A million-dollar choice.</i>

22:40.274 --> 22:41.874
Here I was, worried about your job.

22:41.876 --> 22:43.476
Now I'm worried about mine.

22:43.478 --> 22:45.778
<i>- How soon?
- Any minute now.</i>

22:45.780 --> 22:48.280
<i>- I can see it in his eyes.
- Well, I hope so.</i>

22:48.282 --> 22:50.382
Because you know what else
can ruin a romantic weekend?

22:50.384 --> 22:51.817
A visit from the Doctor.

22:51.819 --> 22:54.754
The Doctor gets his money,
we get our lives.

22:54.756 --> 22:56.455
I know, I know.

22:56.457 --> 22:59.058
Take down the Doctor,
we reclaim the money,

22:59.060 --> 23:01.994
we get our medals, and I go home.

23:01.996 --> 23:04.663
Get it done, Agent Simons. Soon.

23:04.665 --> 23:06.832
- Consider that an order.
- Finish it.

23:06.834 --> 23:08.634
It's time to put this
shitty chapter behind us

23:08.636 --> 23:10.102
<i>and blow out of this town.</i>

23:10.104 --> 23:11.804
Absolutely.

23:17.188 --> 23:20.624
So my cousin and her friends
used quite a bit of grit

23:20.626 --> 23:22.793
and intelligence to find this woman,

23:22.795 --> 23:25.863
but in order to actually
get to her, well,

23:25.865 --> 23:27.364
they have to do a
bunch of illegal stuff.

23:27.366 --> 23:30.367
Just to pay for travel, etcetera.

23:30.369 --> 23:32.336
And then they find out that the FBI

23:32.338 --> 23:35.239
has been onto this con woman
for quite some time.

23:35.241 --> 23:39.176
And they're probably onto
my cousin and her pals.

23:39.178 --> 23:42.880
So that's it. Any ideas?

23:42.882 --> 23:45.215
- Thoughts?
- Well, it crosses state lines.

23:45.217 --> 23:48.919
- Chip, you do federal.
- Okay.

23:48.921 --> 23:51.121
Your cousin doesn't
have a lot of choices.

23:51.123 --> 23:54.224
Yeah, but what I'm talking
about is pure profit.

23:54.226 --> 23:57.261
Yeah, but you have to have
inventory, distribution,

23:57.263 --> 23:58.929
all that pain in the ass stuff.

23:58.931 --> 24:01.064
- We just take our cut...
- You collect crumbs

24:01.066 --> 24:02.733
off the table.

24:02.735 --> 24:04.201
- You don't actually, you know...
- Sell something.

24:04.203 --> 24:07.738
- Yes. Sell something.
- Right? Something real.

24:07.740 --> 24:10.040
Something that a customer
can touch, right?

24:10.042 --> 24:12.843
That I can point at and say,
"Value. Good. Buy."

24:12.845 --> 24:14.445
And then you set the price.

24:14.447 --> 24:16.113
Sounds like an old-fashioned
way of making money to me.

24:16.115 --> 24:17.614
I think I'll stick to
playing the markets.

24:17.616 --> 24:19.783
- Rich is rich in my book.
- Well said.

24:19.785 --> 24:21.003
Hey!

24:22.021 --> 24:23.554
Hey, so sorry to interrupt.

24:23.556 --> 24:25.189
- Can I grab you for a second?
- Yeah, of course.

24:25.191 --> 24:27.024
Real quick, I want you to meet the gang.

24:27.026 --> 24:30.127
This is Kurt, Duke, Bobby.
Guys, this is my friend,

24:30.129 --> 24:32.896
- Jules Langmore.
- Nice to meet you.

24:32.898 --> 24:35.132
Julia Langmore.

24:35.134 --> 24:36.800
Jesus Christ.

24:36.802 --> 24:39.703
- We... we have to go.
- No, no, no.

24:39.705 --> 24:41.472
This should be good.

24:41.474 --> 24:44.308
So, you a big, famous artist yet?

24:44.310 --> 24:46.710
Stealing shit left and right?

24:46.712 --> 24:48.712
Wait, wait, wait.
This... this is that girl?

24:48.714 --> 24:50.647
This was your sister's roommate?

24:50.649 --> 24:53.250
Yeah. This is her.

24:53.252 --> 24:55.052
One classy bitch.

24:55.054 --> 24:56.753
Hey, easy, man.

24:56.755 --> 24:58.388
Why don't we all just
finish our drinks...

24:58.390 --> 25:00.824
- Is this your girlfriend?
- It's my friend, but...

25:00.826 --> 25:02.960
This is a bad person. A fraud.

25:02.962 --> 25:04.561
It's not true. It wasn't my fault.

25:04.563 --> 25:05.963
- It wasn't your fault?
- Hey, hands off, man.

25:05.965 --> 25:07.831
- Be a gentleman.
- Watch what you say to me,

25:07.833 --> 25:09.233
- you dick!
- I will pound your teeth

25:09.235 --> 25:10.901
into your goddamn throat.

25:10.903 --> 25:13.303
All right, all right.
Richard, let him up now.

25:15.741 --> 25:17.608
You should be ashamed of who you are!

25:17.610 --> 25:19.444
All right, man.

25:20.579 --> 25:22.779
Jules? Hey.

25:25.484 --> 25:28.752
Sorry. Hey, what the hell
happened in there?

25:28.754 --> 25:30.621
Nothing. Sorry I messed up
heaven for you.

25:30.623 --> 25:32.856
That's not what I meant. What happened?

25:32.858 --> 25:35.058
No. We are not talking about it.

25:41.800 --> 25:45.469
Honey, you look very handsome
in your denim and leather apron.

25:46.698 --> 25:50.364
I just hope the neighbors
don't have their binoculars out.

25:50.476 --> 25:52.042
I don't know how this is gonna go.

25:52.044 --> 25:53.443
- Sweetie.
- I didn't have

25:53.445 --> 25:55.612
such a good time downstairs
and it was just...

25:55.614 --> 25:58.815
Ours went fine,
and it's gonna be fine, I promise.

25:58.817 --> 26:02.019
If you can keep your temper in check.

26:02.021 --> 26:04.388
- I'll keep my temper in check.
- You will?

26:04.390 --> 26:06.056
- Yes, I promise.
- Okay.

26:06.058 --> 26:07.457
- Thank you.
- Can I get a kiss?

26:07.459 --> 26:10.394
Please do.

26:10.396 --> 26:11.828
It's great to have them both here.

26:15.200 --> 26:17.501
Wait, let me guess. So Josh and Ezra

26:17.503 --> 26:19.002
both needed five stitches each

26:19.004 --> 26:21.338
- and they owed you $20?
- And they never paid!

26:21.340 --> 26:22.706
- I didn't have any money!
- Pretty sure I paid.

26:22.708 --> 26:23.822
I paid.

26:24.476 --> 26:25.976
- Arthur, Arthur, honey.
- Josh got locked

26:25.978 --> 26:27.010
- in the basement.
- No.

26:27.012 --> 26:28.312
Put them out of their misery.

26:28.314 --> 26:31.315
Just give us the news. Okay?

26:31.317 --> 26:32.849
Okay, I suppose it's time.

26:35.888 --> 26:36.763
Um...

26:36.798 --> 26:37.854
- Very serious.
- Official.

26:37.856 --> 26:40.357
I've gathered you all together
here because, as you know,

26:40.359 --> 26:41.825
I have a big announcement to make.

26:41.827 --> 26:43.093
Wait, an announcement?

26:43.095 --> 26:44.528
You never mentioned that to us.

26:44.530 --> 26:46.330
- With...
- God. The Three Stooges.

26:46.332 --> 26:49.032
Everything that's been going
on in our family lately,

26:49.034 --> 26:51.234
um, combined with my attack,

26:51.236 --> 26:54.949
I've been thinking a
lot about priorities.

26:55.894 --> 27:00.063
You know, you just spend all day
thinking about the next thing.

27:00.065 --> 27:02.999
The one you think is gonna
be bigger or brighter.

27:03.001 --> 27:05.568
And you can lose sight of what you have.

27:05.570 --> 27:07.237
How valuable it is.

27:07.239 --> 27:09.205
How it could all go away.

27:09.207 --> 27:12.175
And life, as they say,
is for the living.

27:12.177 --> 27:14.945
So, for years,
your mother and I have been

27:14.947 --> 27:16.880
talking about taking a trip.

27:16.882 --> 27:19.115
- A second honeymoon.
- You have?

27:19.117 --> 27:21.751
To whom, exactly,
have you spoken about this?

27:21.753 --> 27:23.453
Well, you don't know
everything about us,

27:23.455 --> 27:24.754
- then, do you?
- Apparently not.

27:24.756 --> 27:26.748
So now, now...

27:27.426 --> 27:29.392
God damn it, we're gonna do it.

27:29.394 --> 27:31.761
We're taking six months
and we're just going.

27:31.763 --> 27:33.897
- Six months?
- Yes, if you're gonna charter

27:33.899 --> 27:35.966
a boat in the Mediterranean,
you may as well

27:35.968 --> 27:38.301
make it worth your while.

27:38.303 --> 27:39.903
- Seriously?
- Yeah.

27:39.905 --> 27:41.071
Wow. I'm so happy you guys are going.

27:41.073 --> 27:42.595
- You so deserve it.
- Wait.

27:42.596 --> 27:43.583
What's gonna happen with the company

27:43.584 --> 27:45.753
- while you're gone?
- Well, he's getting to that.

27:46.261 --> 27:48.959
- Slowly.
- You boys are smart.

27:48.960 --> 27:49.960
You have integrity.

27:51.339 --> 27:53.101
You treat people well.

27:54.450 --> 27:59.691
You've grown into men
that I'm proud to call my sons.

27:59.872 --> 28:01.938
You're not actually dying, are you, Dad?

28:01.940 --> 28:04.341
- That's very funny, Josh.
- You wanna know who's dying?

28:04.343 --> 28:07.043
I'm dying! Come on, get with it!

28:07.045 --> 28:10.847
Your mother and I have
decided that we would like

28:10.849 --> 28:14.050
the two of you... with Gaby's help...

28:14.052 --> 28:17.420
to start taking over
the family business.

28:17.422 --> 28:19.422
What?

28:19.424 --> 28:21.124
We thought you were never gonna leave.

28:21.126 --> 28:24.027
Yeah, mostly because you said,
"I will never leave.

28:24.029 --> 28:25.762
They can wheel me out."

28:25.764 --> 28:28.365
I had a change of heart.

28:28.367 --> 28:30.066
It happens.

28:30.068 --> 28:35.872
Sometimes the life you want
is right in front of you.

28:35.874 --> 28:39.142
You just have to see it.

28:39.144 --> 28:41.077
And take it.

28:50.088 --> 28:52.923
Am I weird for wanting to
stay in with you all the time

28:52.925 --> 28:56.259
rather than going to some fancy,
shmancy place?

28:56.261 --> 29:00.096
No. No, I don't think you're weird.

29:00.098 --> 29:01.533
Really?

29:02.835 --> 29:04.437
How about now?

29:05.604 --> 29:06.876
No.

29:07.606 --> 29:08.939
- No?
- No.

29:11.677 --> 29:13.944
- Now?
- No, that's not weird.

29:13.946 --> 29:16.179
I-I do that all the time.

29:16.181 --> 29:19.649
- Now?
- Disgusting, but not weird.

29:20.986 --> 29:22.752
But you know what?
Now that you mention it...

29:22.754 --> 29:25.589
- What?
- There is something strange.

29:25.591 --> 29:27.257
I knew it. It's my big toe, isn't it?

29:27.259 --> 29:30.093
- No... well, yeah.
- Hey!

29:30.095 --> 29:32.362
- What is it?
- It's your hands.

29:32.364 --> 29:34.798
- My hands are not weird!
- Yeah, no, they are.

29:34.800 --> 29:36.299
- Here, look.
- No!

29:36.301 --> 29:38.702
Come here, let me see.

29:38.704 --> 29:40.437
- What?
- Look.

29:40.439 --> 29:44.507
See, now... your hands look perfect.

29:45.731 --> 29:48.378
My God.

29:48.380 --> 29:51.114
It's a saffron.

29:51.116 --> 29:54.517
I've never seen one before.

29:54.519 --> 29:56.052
They're crazy rare, right?

29:59.024 --> 30:00.457
Crazy rare.

30:03.228 --> 30:06.863
You are the most incredible,

30:06.865 --> 30:09.799
fascinating woman I've ever met.

30:09.801 --> 30:15.338
And I know a life with
you would be beautiful.

30:15.340 --> 30:18.742
And I know that we would
laugh every single day.

30:18.744 --> 30:23.613
Saffron Keyes, will you marry me?

30:28.013 --> 30:29.452
No.

30:32.341 --> 30:34.575
- No?
- No.

30:34.577 --> 30:36.744
I have a counter proposal.

30:36.746 --> 30:39.247
You do?

30:39.249 --> 30:41.382
Let's run away together.

30:41.384 --> 30:43.051
You and me. Tonight.

30:43.053 --> 30:45.119
You don't have any obligations.

30:45.121 --> 30:47.121
I don't have any that I care about.

30:47.123 --> 30:50.458
Yeah, but I mean, how...
how would that even work?

30:50.460 --> 30:53.528
We just take the jet and disappear?

30:53.530 --> 30:55.530
- Yeah.
- Start new lives?

30:55.532 --> 30:58.466
Yeah. Patrick, I love you.
Do you love me?

30:58.468 --> 31:01.469
- I do. I love you.
- Okay.

31:01.471 --> 31:03.905
Let's just go, now. Tonight.

31:03.907 --> 31:07.575
We don't have to live
by anyone else's rules.

31:07.577 --> 31:11.479
I mean, isn't that what
you've been searching for?

31:27.964 --> 31:30.898
I can't do that.

31:30.900 --> 31:34.669
I don't... I don't know if it's
my mother's voice in my head

31:34.671 --> 31:37.972
or all the Sundays I spent in church,

31:37.974 --> 31:39.407
but I need...

31:43.246 --> 31:46.013
I guess I'm just traditional.

31:50.320 --> 31:53.421
I guess I'm just not.

32:08.805 --> 32:13.374
If you add it all up, Maddie
could get 30-40 years in prison.

32:13.376 --> 32:15.009
What about us?

32:15.011 --> 32:17.178
They say we'll maybe do five.

32:17.180 --> 32:18.780
- Five years?
- Years.

32:18.782 --> 32:21.048
- My God.
- Yeah.

32:21.050 --> 32:22.590
But there is one more thing.

32:22.591 --> 32:25.520
If we're willing to work with the FBI

32:25.522 --> 32:27.688
to bring Maddie to justice...

32:27.690 --> 32:29.690
We could make a deal.

32:29.692 --> 32:32.493
- Okay.
- Do probation,

32:32.495 --> 32:33.661
not serve any time.

32:33.663 --> 32:35.863
Could you do that?

32:35.865 --> 32:39.200
Put the woman that you love behind bars?

32:39.202 --> 32:44.205
Well, I'd know
where she is all the time.

32:44.207 --> 32:48.843
I could visit her. Bring her magazines.

32:48.845 --> 32:50.711
Maybe she'd finally
do crosswords with me.

32:50.713 --> 32:52.980
She never would before.

32:52.982 --> 32:54.549
And then maybe we could finally...

32:56.486 --> 32:58.049
Yeah, stupid idea.

32:59.355 --> 33:04.425
Hey, um, thanks for having
my back there at the club.

33:06.529 --> 33:08.996
Yeah, the code's the code, right?

33:08.998 --> 33:11.616
Pretty sure that's not in the code.

33:13.002 --> 33:15.570
Well, you're welcome, then.

33:19.275 --> 33:21.342
That stuff they were talking about,

33:21.344 --> 33:23.444
that's what was in your envelope?

33:23.446 --> 33:24.812
In the freezer?

33:34.290 --> 33:36.732
My mom was just so sick.

33:38.361 --> 33:42.530
And, you know,
I didn't know what to do.

33:42.532 --> 33:44.031
This guy comes to me,

33:44.033 --> 33:49.537
talking about shaving
some points and money.

33:53.109 --> 33:54.809
- I don't know.
- Hey.

33:57.113 --> 33:59.146
We do what we have to do.

34:01.951 --> 34:04.418
- You wanna talk about...
- My envelope stays sealed.

34:07.574 --> 34:09.223
So what do we do now?

34:09.225 --> 34:10.757
We gotta call Ezra.

34:10.760 --> 34:13.393
What if our phones are tapped?

34:15.440 --> 34:16.831
We'll text him.

34:16.833 --> 34:19.600
Pretty sure they can track that, too.

34:19.601 --> 34:21.469
We'll text him in code.

34:21.471 --> 34:23.304
- Come on.
- Okay.

34:34.984 --> 34:37.418
Yo, I was thinking, because I'm older,

34:37.420 --> 34:40.187
I should have Dad's office
and you should have Mom's.

34:40.188 --> 34:44.257
You do know Mom's a year older than Dad.

34:44.260 --> 34:46.360
Right, right.

34:46.362 --> 34:49.630
No problem. It's all yours.

34:49.632 --> 34:52.466
For reals?

34:52.467 --> 34:55.803
Shit, man. You're gonna back out.

34:55.804 --> 34:57.705
They just offered us
the fricking company.

34:57.707 --> 35:00.675
Look, I thought you wanted to
go to Denmark and be like Dink.

35:00.677 --> 35:02.343
I can be Dink right here.

35:02.345 --> 35:04.679
This is like my Dink moment.

35:04.681 --> 35:06.847
And you?

35:06.849 --> 35:08.849
You know...

35:08.851 --> 35:11.118
we would be like...

35:11.120 --> 35:13.354
I just... I don't know if I can do it.

35:13.356 --> 35:15.489
Okay. But you're not saying no.

35:15.491 --> 35:17.158
No, just think about it.

35:17.160 --> 35:20.628
Do not let this go.
'Cause we would kill it, man.

35:20.630 --> 35:23.264
As brothers. You know?

35:24.667 --> 35:26.167
Hey, Ezra the human, you wanna go walk.

35:26.169 --> 35:28.836
- Ezra the dog with me?
- Sure.

35:28.838 --> 35:32.306
- And around they go again.
- Shut up, Josh.

35:34.744 --> 35:36.410
So then he walks in the exam room

35:36.412 --> 35:40.381
and he's like, "Hi, I'm Dr. Sheffield,
the vetinarian." And I'm like,

35:40.383 --> 35:42.483
- "You mean the veterinarian?"
- Yeah.

35:42.485 --> 35:44.218
And he looks at me like
I'm pronouncing it wrong.

35:44.220 --> 35:45.553
- That's nuts.
- No, it gets crazier.

35:45.555 --> 35:47.822
Later that day, I went to return a book

35:47.824 --> 35:49.290
and there was this woman
that I didn't recognize

35:49.292 --> 35:50.658
sitting at the desk and she's like,

35:50.660 --> 35:53.394
"Hi, I'm Mrs. Jones, the new libarian."

35:53.396 --> 35:55.029
- No!
- Like, you have to be able

35:55.031 --> 35:56.593
to pronounce your own job.

35:56.666 --> 35:57.898
- It should be a requirement.
- Yeah.

35:57.900 --> 35:59.600
- At the very least.
- Sorry.

35:59.602 --> 36:01.435
My friends think they're
being funny or something.

36:01.437 --> 36:02.770
Do you have new friends?

36:02.772 --> 36:04.605
- Yeah.
- Wow.

36:04.607 --> 36:07.241
- You got a problem with that?
- No, it's just so fancy.

36:09.412 --> 36:12.179
It's pretty crazy
about your mom and dad?

36:12.181 --> 36:13.614
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

36:13.616 --> 36:16.450
Um, you know,
Josh wants to do it and I think

36:16.452 --> 36:18.786
it could be really good.

36:18.788 --> 36:22.523
- It's just, um...
- What?

36:22.525 --> 36:24.892
Part of me thinks I need
to finish what I started

36:24.894 --> 36:27.595
with my so-called ex-wife.

36:27.597 --> 36:29.599
Did you just roll your eyes at me?

36:31.401 --> 36:34.068
Sorry. I don't know
what they're playing at.

36:34.070 --> 36:37.471
You know what? What your dad
said is pretty spot on, Ezra.

36:37.473 --> 36:38.939
I hope it doesn't take you 30 years

36:38.941 --> 36:40.541
of whatever you're doing to realize

36:40.543 --> 36:42.910
what you have standing
right in front of you.

36:45.248 --> 36:48.449
Maybe.

36:48.451 --> 36:49.650
Maybe it won't.

36:51.387 --> 36:53.587
- Actually, my ride's here.
- Yeah?

36:53.589 --> 36:55.790
I see you've made

36:55.792 --> 36:58.325
new friends, too.

36:58.327 --> 37:01.429
To be determined.

37:01.431 --> 37:04.365
Maybe I'll see you at the office.

37:26.665 --> 37:28.198
Got a 1:00 tee time. You in?

37:28.200 --> 37:31.034
Ooh, isn't that a pretty long lunch?

37:31.036 --> 37:32.936
Wait. We're the boss.

37:35.600 --> 37:37.040
<i>Check your top drawer.</i>

37:40.011 --> 37:42.345
<i>It's blueberry peach.</i>

37:42.347 --> 37:44.781
<i>- Who's better than you?
- No one.</i>

38:03.668 --> 38:04.901
Ezra, no!

38:19.718 --> 38:20.750
<i>- Hello?
- Bro!</i>

38:20.752 --> 38:22.252
Why have you not texted us back?

38:22.254 --> 38:24.921
You were, like, butt-emojing me.

38:24.923 --> 38:26.990
It wasn't butt emoji, it was code!

38:26.992 --> 38:29.959
Frog, bikini, Eiffel Tower is FBI.

38:29.961 --> 38:31.694
Eiffel Tower is spelled with an E.

38:31.696 --> 38:33.496
What? Eiffel Tower?
That's not the point, man.

38:33.498 --> 38:36.733
- The point is that...
- Ez, this is serious.

38:36.735 --> 38:38.568
Patrick is in the FBI.

38:38.570 --> 38:40.203
Wait. What?

38:40.205 --> 38:41.738
<i>The Feds are trying to take Maddie down.</i>

38:41.740 --> 38:43.406
They could come after us, too. Okay.

38:43.408 --> 38:45.675
Look, man. We need you back, like, now.

38:45.677 --> 38:47.043
<i>- Just come now.
- All right.</i>

38:47.045 --> 38:49.279
All right, calm down.

38:49.281 --> 38:53.516
Everything's gonna be okay.

38:53.518 --> 38:55.051
Okay?

39:11.703 --> 39:13.303
- Airport, please.
- You got it.

39:20.812 --> 39:24.047
Granola bar?

39:24.049 --> 39:27.050
Je suis desole, madame.
Je ne parle pas Anglais.

39:27.052 --> 39:29.419
I'm sorry.

